The global trade in endangered species faces challenges, with coral reefs particularly at risk due to overexploitation.
Species like Brazilian lobsters and sawfish are under threat, prompting calls for protection.
Deforestation of cedar trees in South and Central America has led to trade restrictions.
The UN Environment Programme highlights the dangers of habitat destruction and climate change.
Conservation efforts are crucial to safeguard marine ecosystems, with coral reefs serving as vital habitats.
Sustainable practices are essential to ensure the survival of coral species and protect the valuable red coral industry.
The tourism industry plays a role in raising awareness and supporting conservation efforts for coral reefs.
